The SKILL.md file is the **GOLD SKILL** master specification for the `mini-theory-of-computation` project. Here's a summary of its key contents:

---

## Core Philosophy
> **知识覆盖率 = 完成标准。代码量 = 准入门槛。两者缺一不可。**
> (Knowledge coverage = completion standard. Code volume = entry threshold. Both are indispensable.)

## Dual Standard
Each sub-module (e.g. `mini-acc0-circuits/`) must satisfy **both**:
- **Entry condition**: ≥3,000 lines of production code (`include/` + `src/`) per sub-module (excluding tests, examples, Lean files)
- **Completion condition**: L1–L6 Complete + L7–L9 Partial across the nine knowledge levels

## Nine Knowledge Levels (L1–L9)
| L1 | Definitions | P, NP, Turing machine, circuit family |
| L2 | Core Concepts | polynomial time, non-determinism, hierarchy |
| L3 | Math Structures | Turing machine tuples, Boolean circuit DAGs, CNF/DNF |
| L4 | Fundamental Theorems | Cook-Levin, Time Hierarchy, Savitch, Ladner |
| L5 | Algorithms | DPLL/CDCL, switching lemma, IP=PSPACE |
| L6 | Canonical Problems | SAT, 3SAT, VERTEX-COVER, PARITY |
| L7 | Applications | cryptography, formal verification, PAC learning |
| L8 | Advanced Topics | PCP Theorem, natural proofs barrier |
| L9 | Research Frontiers | meta-complexity, GCT, quantum complexity |

## Nine-School Curriculum Alignment
MIT · Stanford · Berkeley · CMU · Princeton · Caltech · Cambridge · Oxford · ETH

## Mandatory Structure per Sub-Module
```
mini-xxx/
├── Makefile, README.md
├── include/ (≥4 headers)
├── src/ (≥4 C files + ≥1 Lean file)
├── tests/ (assert-based)
├── examples/ (≥3 runnable)
├── demos/, benches/
└── docs/ (knowledge-graph.md, coverage-report.md, gap-report.md,
          course-alignment.md, course-tree.md)
```

## Strict Anti-Filler Rules
Zero tolerance for padding: no `_fn1.._fnN`, `_aux1.._auxN`, `_ext1.._extN` patterns, no copied stub blocks in Lean, no `by trivial` on non-trivial propositions, no `sorry` in complete modules.

## Completion Scoring
- Each L1–L9 layer scored: Complete (2), Partial (1), Missing (0)
- **COMPLETE**: ≥16/18 with L1≠Missing, L4≠Missing, ≥6 layers Complete
- Safety review (filler scan, stub scan, empty file scan, doc completeness, self-consistency) must pass before declaring COMPLETE.
